orientation = Orientation(Side.RIGHT, Side.TOP)
rotations = list(orientation.iterate_rotations(keeping))
assert len(expected) == len(rotations)
assert {Orientation(a, b) for a, b in expected} == set(rotations)
pytest.mark.parametrize('keeping, expected', [(Side.FRONT, {(R, T), (R, F),
    (R, B), (R, D)}), (Side.BOTTOM, {(R, T), (F, T), (L, T), (B, T)}), (
    Side.LEFT, {(R, T), (T, L), (L, D), (D, R)}), (None, {(F, T), (F, R), (
    F, L), (F, D), (R, T), (R, F), (R, B), (R, D), (B, T), (B, L), (B, R),
    (B, D), (L, T), (L, F), (L, B), (L, D), (T, F), (T, L), (T, R), (T, B),
    (D, F), (D, L), (D, R), (D, B)})])
